data.content:
Here's the xUnit equivalent:

**Key mappings:**
- `[SetUp]` → constructor
- `[TearDown]` → `IDisposable.Dispose`
- `[OneTimeSetUp]`/`[OneTimeTearDown]` → `IClassFixture<T>` with a fixture class

```csharp
// Shared fixture for one-time setup/teardown
public class DatabaseFixture : IDisposable
{
    public DatabaseFixture()
    {
        Database.Initialize();
    }

    public void Dispose()
    {
        Database.Cleanup();
    }
}

// Test class uses constructor/Dispose for per-test setup/teardown
public class CustomerRepositoryTests : IClassFixture<DatabaseFixture>, IDisposable
{
    private readonly DbContext _context;
    private readonly CustomerRepository _repo;

    public CustomerRepositoryTests(DatabaseFixture fixture)
    {
        // Per-test setup (replaces [SetUp])
        _context = new TestDbContext();
        _repo = new CustomerRepository(_context);
    }

    public void Dispose()
    {
        // Per-test teardown (replaces [TearDown])
        _context.Dispose();
    }

    [Fact]
    public void FindById_ExistingCustomer_ReturnsCustomer()
    {
        var customer = _repo.FindById(1);
        Assert.NotNull(customer);
        Assert.Equal("Alice", customer.Name);
    }
}
```

**Summary:**
| NUnit | xUnit |
|-------|-------|
| `[OneTimeSetUp]` | `IClassFixture<T>` constructor |
| `[OneTimeTearDown]` | Fixture's `Dispose` |
| `[SetUp]` | Test class constructor |
| `[TearDown]` | `IDisposable.Dispose` |

The `DatabaseFixture` instance is created once and shared across all tests in the class. The test class constructor/`Dispose` run for every test. If you need async teardown, implement `IAsyncDisposable` with `DisposeAsync` instead.
